---
title: Data Toolbox
description: A practical toolbox of scraping, wrangling, analysis and visualisation resources for data journalism.
navLabel: Data Toolbox
section: Resources
order: 20
---

Initially based on [a list by Prof. Bahareh Heravi](https://nitter.net/Bahareh360), with some additions from me. You can find [an even larger list on SPJ Toolbox](https://www.journaliststoolbox.org/category/data-visualization-and-online-tools/).

## Collection

- [Web Scraper](https://webscraper.io/) - Browser plugin for scraping.
- [Outwit Hub](https://www.outwit.com/products/hub/OutWit-Hub-Light-Pro-Expert-Enterprise-editions) - Desktop app for scraping.
- [Parsehub](https://www.parsehub.com/) - Desktop app for scraping.
- [Visualping](https://visualping.io/) - Monitor website changes.
- [Tabula](http://tabula.technology/) - Get data from PDFs.
- [WebPlotDigitize](https://aps.automeris.io/wpd/) - Digitise chart images.
- [Map Digitizer](https://mapster.me/map-digitizer/) - Digitise image maps.
- [IFTTT](https://ifttt.com/) - Automate tasks.
- [NodeXL](http://www.smrfoundation.org/nodexl/) - Network analysis.
- [Media Cloud](https://www.mediacloud.org/) - Media analysis.
- [R](https://rvest.tidyverse.org/) / [rvest](https://rvest.tidyverse.org/) - Programming language and scraping library.
- [Python](https://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/) / [BeautifulSoup](https://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/) - Programming language and scraping library.
- [Selenium](https://www.selenium.dev/) - Browser automation.
- [curl converter](https://curlconverter.com/) - Convert curl commands to Python, JS, R and more.
- [SelectorGadget](https://selectorgadget.com/) - CSS selector helper.
- [data.page](https://data.page/json/csv) - JSON to CSV converter.
- [SVG Crowbar](https://nytimes.github.io/svg-crowbar/) - Lift SVGs off webpages.

## FOIA

- [FOIA Wiki](https://foia.wiki/wiki/Main_Page) - FOIA resources with a US focus.
- [Data Liberation Project](https://www.data-liberation-project.org/) - Released government datasets.
- [WhatDoTheyKnow](https://www.whatdotheyknow.com/) - FOIA tool and catalogue.

## Wrangling

- [Microsoft Excel](https://www.microsoft.com/en-gb/microsoft-365/excel) - Desktop spreadsheet app.
- [Google Sheets](https://www.google.com/sheets/about/) - Free web-based spreadsheet app.
- [OpenRefine](http://openrefine.org/) - Data cleaning and transformation.
- [Parserator](https://parserator.datamade.us/) - Parse addresses and other unstructured text.
- [Geocodio](https://www.geocod.io/) - Geocode US and Canadian addresses.

## Analysis

- [Microsoft Excel](https://www.microsoft.com/en-gb/microsoft-365/excel) - Desktop spreadsheet app.
- [Google Sheets](https://www.google.com/sheets/about/) - Free web-based spreadsheet app.
- [R](https://rvest.tidyverse.org/) / [rvest](https://rvest.tidyverse.org/) - Programming language and library ecosystem.
- [Python](https://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/) / [BeautifulSoup](https://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/) - Programming language and scraping library.
- [SPSS](https://www.ibm.com/spss) - Statistical analysis software.
- [PSPP](https://www.gnu.org/software/pspp/) - Statistical analysis software.
- [Tableau](https://www.tableau.com/) - Paid data analysis and visualisation tool.
- [QGIS](https://qgis.org/en/site/) - Desktop mapping software.
- [CARTO](https://carto.com/) - Web mapping software.

## Visualisation

- [Datawrapper](http://datawrapper.de/) - Web dataviz tool.
- [Flourish](http://flourish.studio/) - Web interactive/dataviz tool.
- [RAW Graphs](https://www.rawgraphs.io/) - Static chart maker.
- [Infogram](https://infogram.com/) - Infographic creator.
- [Datamatic.io](http://datamatic.io/) - Web dataviz tool.
- [Highcharts](https://www.highcharts.com/) - Chart library for developers.
- [Plotly](https://plot.ly/) - Chart library for developers.
- [D3.js](https://d3js.org/) - Library for advanced dataviz.
- [Mapbox](https://www.mapbox.com/) - Mapping platform.
- [Mapshaper](https://mapshaper.org/) - Editor for map data.
- [geojson.io](https://geojson.io/) - Editor for map data.
- [Gephi](https://gephi.org/) - Network visualisations.
- [R](https://www.r-project.org/) / [ggplot2](http://ggplot2.org/) - Programming language and visualisation library.

### Colours

- [ColorBrewer](https://colorbrewer2.org) - Safe colour palette collection.
- [Chroma.js](https://gka.github.io/palettes/) - Colour palette helper.
- [Scientific Colour Maps](https://www.fabiocrameri.ch/colourmaps/) - Colour-blind-safe and perceptually accurate palettes.
